Cuticle thin, less than 2 μm thick throughout. Body wall thick but soft and relatively transparent. No thickened septa. Brain (
Figure 5A
) oval, with shallow anterior convexity, 
in vivo
190–204 by 135–146 μm. Peptonephridia ending in VI or VII, each consisting of a stout stem giving off many thin, long, equal-sized, straight branches at two distinct levels, proximally (or at midlength) and terminally (
type
c sensu
Nielsen and Christensen, 1959
) (
Figure 6D
). Pharyngeal glands four pairs, three of which partly merging dorsally at 4/5–6/7, plus extra lobes ventral in VII (
Figure 6A
). Five pairs of preclitellar nephridia (6/7–10/11), with efferent ducts arising antero- to midventrally from postseptal.
